n": "NONE", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "I discovered a problem when voxelizing complex geometries ([nasal_cavity.ply.zip](https://github.com/mikedh/trimesh/files/2254037/nasal_cavity.ply.zip)). The problem is visible in the following comparison of the original geometry (shown in red) and the voxelized geometry shown translucently in gray:\r\n\r\n![voxels](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/5444873/43593437-03a1c268-9678-11e8-970a-9d42e5791060.png)\r\n\r\nApparently, the voxelization adds vertical bands that are not present in the original geometry. The code I used to generate the voxelization is\r\n\r\n```python\r\nmesh = trimesh.load('nasal_cavity.ply')\r\nprint(mesh.is_watertight)\r\nmesh_discretized = mesh.voxelized(pitch=1, max_iter=None)\r\nvoxels = mesh_discretized.marching_cubes\r\nvoxels.export('nasal_cavity_voxels.ply')\r\n```\r\n\r\nI also tried different values for `pitch` and I used `method='ray'`, but I observed similar effects for all settings. Is there any hope to achieve a proper voxelization of this geometry?\r\n", "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/mikedh/trimesh/issues/200/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/mikedh/trimesh/issues/200/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null, "state_reason": "completed"}]